#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Children gather in a  community hall every week to fill the room with the most beautiful sound. For a few hours of practice every week it is the safe space for these members of The Rosa Junior Choir. They get to experience the freedom and joy of singing. READ: Imilonji Kantu Choir Society to sing for the late Archbishop Desmond Tutu The choir was formed by nonprofit organisation, Cape Cultural Collective aiming to promote collective development and unite people and across the Cape. Under the watchful eye of qualified music teacher, Tersia the Rosa Choir are taught songs across our official languages, singing in English, isiXhosa and Afrikaans. However, with every success comes challenges too. Watch the video above for more details on this story.